<br>
Need - A piece of equipment that will raise primary statistics for that character. Primary statistics are those stats that have a direct effect on the characters abilities in RvR and hunting situations. For example, Rogues, stealth, dex, quick, envenom and leather armor but NOT str, con or int. <br>
<br>
Highest level player with a &quot;need&quot; gets first rights to a loot drop. This is to use only. If the item can be immediately used, then it is customary to hand the gear it replaced to another in the group who would have a need. This way the group gets stronger, the guild gets stronger, and Hibernia gets stronger. <br>
<br>
Higher level players will &quot;grey&quot; out to any given encounter sooner as well and will have less chances to obtain that same item then the lower level player.<br>
<br>
If an equal need takes place (two or more players of the same level, with the same need for an item), then the item must be randomed. This must be done so each has an equal chance to obtain the item, and so there is no question. Unfortunately, DAoC does not have a /random feature at this time. But there are ways!<br>
<br>
One method I have used to good effect is the coin drop method. One player pick &quot;odd&quot; and another &quot;even&quot;. When the next coin drops, the copper will be odd or even. Everyone in a group always gets the same amount of coin from a monster drop so there is no question. If there are 3 or more, then split it up. Player #1 1-33; #2 34-66, #3 67-99 - 00 is re-roll. You get the idea. <br>
<br>
Officers - Silver Hawk Officers are committed to their guild members well-being. If an equal need occurs between Silver Hawks, the higher ranked person will defer to the guild member. This is for fully pledged Hawks and not Initiates. <br>
<br>
Grouping - Silver Hawk groups (SH formed and/or majority) will divvy up the loot Need before Greed style, as outlined here. <br>
<br>
If you happen join a group of non-Hawks, be sure to ask if the loot is Need Before Greed when joining. Most times, that is what everyone will go with in Hibernia. If they don't, then it's up to you whether you want to stay in that group. Be respectful of others desire to manage loot differently.<br>
<br>
If you don't agree with it, then your option is to not join the group<br>
